sequenceDiagram
  %% Agentic Delivery Framework â€” Planning & Delivery Sequence (GitHub profile)
  participant DL as Delivery Lead (GitHub App)
  participant GH as GitHub Projects (Sprints)
  participant CS as GitHub Codespaces
  participant DEV as Developers (workspace)
  participant PRG as Pull Request Gates

  DL->>GH: Select active Sprint & Stories
  DL->>CS: Create/Resume Codespace (prebuilds, secrets)
  DL->>DEV: Start session via `gh codespace ssh -c`
  DEV->>CS: git switch -c feat/&lt;issue-key&gt;
  DEV->>DEV: Implement slices (edit/run/test)
  DEV->>PRG: Open PR with "Closes #&lt;issue-id&gt;" + Story Preview
  PRG->>PRG: CI / QA Verification / Security Review / Automated Review / Human Review / Performance Budget
  alt All gates pass
    PRG->>CS: Merge to default branch (Increment meets DoD)
    DL->>GH: Move Story to Done; publish Pulse Increment
    DL->>CS: Stop/Hibernate Codespace if idle
  else Any gate fails
    PRG->>DEV: Comments & failing checks
    DEV->>CS: Iterate fixes on branch
  end
  DL->>GH: Sprint Review & plan next Sprint
